{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2e6ef941-a76f-4cb1-a76f-6ee498ad208c","content":"Here's the mapping from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/*[Tag=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n| VSTest flag | New platform flag |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/*[Tag=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test projects):\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\n**Project file** — enable the new runner:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThe `--` separator tells `dotnet test` to forward everything after it directly to the new test platform runner.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"989d3df4-ce4d-4ee0-b019-4bdf08f8f537","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a codebase task. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same, but may need `--` prefix for MSTest runner)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with coverage format options\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nThe Microsoft.Testing.Platform command structure differs from VSTest in several ways. Filter syntax can use `--filter` for VSTest compatibility or `--treenode-filter` for the new format, while TRX reporting uses `--report-trx` instead of the logger option.\n\nCode coverage shifts to `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura`, and the blame options become `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with timeout support. Each of these features requires its corresponding extension package. When running with `dotnet test` and the new platform, some of these options behave differently than they did with the older test runner. I'm realizing the key difference is whether you're using the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner with the proper project configuration, which changes how arguments get passed through `dotnet test` to the underlying platform. The syntax and available options shift depending on which runner is actually active, and I need to clarify which setup the user is working with before giving the exact command. I'm seeing the complete mapping table now, showing how each VSTest option translates to the Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalent, and I can construct the full command that combines all these flags together for integration testing with coverage and diagnostics enabled.","outputTokens":1652,"requestId":"CFE5:18DC54:5CBE7BD:6800E10:69EC0EEC"},"id":"998b64e3-76f0-4552-b3c1-841a95a8c624","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:47:02.259Z","parentId":"43e9713f-8775-4100-beb6-3950897eea80"}
